### Step 1: Use the complement rule
The probability of an event and the probability of its complement (i.e., the event not occurring) always add up to 1:

$$
P(A) + P(\text{not } A) = 1
$$

### Step 2: Solve for $ P(\text{not } A) $
$$
P(\text{not } A) = 1 - P(A)
$$

$$
P(\text{not } A) = 1 - 0.3 = 0.7
$$

\boxed{0.7}
